      <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">A more structured reference point that shows why Serralunga matters. It brings firmer tannin, darker shape, and a stricter finish, which makes it useful for learning the serious side of the region and for understanding why some Barolo needs patience.</p>
      <p class="text-xs text-wine-600 mt-2"><strong>Variety:</strong> Nebbiolo</p>
    </div>
